survey_response.review_text: My family's known Dr.Jayashree Sharma for quite a few years now. And our experience during our visits to see her has been consistent in the following way. Firstly, she has a warm personality and a pleasant demeanor. She is a really good listener and she has always been very receptive to every concern and worry any of us had and took her time to explain and ressure us. She is constantly thorough in her examination. She usually takes ample time to explain a condition, makes sure we've understood well before she moves onto treatment options. She never fails to lay out all of the options available, highlight the pros and cons for each one before she gives her opinion on the best suited option for our family member who is the patient, and she also encourages to think it over well before making a decision. She keeps up with the latest proven forms of treatment options. It's worth mentioning that she was the first and only Doctor to suggest a less invasive option and an alternative to surgery when my mother was diagnosed with Adenomyosis and was initially advised to have a hysterectomy. The suggested option involved Emily, an intrauterine device that periodically released hormones to help control excessive endometrial growth which resulted in heavy bleeding. It worked well for my mother. She has helped me put behind a case of persistent UTAs which kept coming back for no discernable reason. Every appointment with her ends with ample and practical advice from her for overall health and lifestyle.

THE "FLORENCE NIGHTINGALE" GYNEC DOCTOR (not a nurse)
Being diabetic I was being treated gingerly by most hospitals that asked me to find an expert gynecologist to remove my uterus since I was diagnosed with adenomyosis and had already had C-sections.
Dr. Jayashree was a god-sent savior who had a no-nonsense clear-headed approach to the medical issues at hand - giving me a week of insulin shots recommendation to bring down the sugar levels so that the surgery could be carried out.
What speeded up my recovery from the expertly conducted laparoscopic surgery - hysterectomy, ovary (with cyst) removed that wasn't spotted earlier, and hernia (again not found previously in diagnostic checkup) patched up - was THE LOVE AND PERSONAL ATTENTION provided.
Last but not the least I was required to be hospitalized for just two days (one day prior and on surgery day) at Sunrays Laparascopic Centre, Ashok Nagar.
I vouch whole-heartedly for the professionalism of Dr. Jayashree Sharma and loved the whole experience of getting back to hale and hearty!
